PROMPT: Which of the following senses is correct for the word "English" in the following text:

 The art of change-ringing is peculiar to the English , and , like most English peculiarities , unintelligible to the rest of the world .

I) an Indo-European language belonging to the West Germanic branch; the official language of Britain and the United States and most of the commonwealth countries
II) the people of England
III) the discipline that studies the English language and literature
IV) (sports) the spin given to a ball by striking it on one side or releasing it with a sharp twist

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: I
Gold answer: 2
========

 The art of change-ringing is peculiar to the English , and , like most English peculiarities , unintelligible to the rest of the world .

I) an odd or unusual characteristic
II) a distinguishing trait
III) something unusual -- perhaps worthy of collecting

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: I
Gold answer: 2
========

I) express in speech
II) exchange thoughts; talk with
III) use language
IV) give a speech to
V) make a characteristic or natural sound

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: V
Gold answer: 3
========

PROMPT: Which of the following senses is correct for the word "belfry" in the following text:

 More often than not , ringers think of the church as something stuck on the bottom of the belfry .

Do not provide explanations.

I) a person who rings church bells (as for summoning the congregation)
II) a person who is almost identical to another
III) a contestant entered in a competition under false pretenses
IV) (horseshoes) the successful throw of a horseshoe or quoit so as to encircle a stake or peg

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 1
========

III) a process of becoming larger or longer or more numerous or more important

V) the gradual beginning or coming forth

VII) something grown or growing

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: III

I) act of improving by expanding or enlarging or refining
II) a process in which something passes by degrees to a different stage (especially a more advanced or mature stage)
III) (biology) the process of an individual organism growing organically; a purely biological unfolding of events involved in an organism changing gradually from a simple to a more complex level
IV) a recent event that has some relevance for the present situation
V) the act of making some area of land or water more profitable or productive or useful
VI) a district that has been developed to serve some purpose
VII) a state in which things are improving; the result of developing (as in the early part of a game of chess)
VIII) processing a photosensitive material in order to make an image visible
IX) (music) the section of a composition or movement (especially in sonata form) where the major musical themes are developed and elaborated

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 3
========

I) relating to or applicable to or concerned with the administration of a city or town or district rather than a larger area
II) of or belonging to or characteristic of a particular locality or neighborhood
III) affecting only a restricted part or area of the body

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 1
========

I) in actual fact
II) used to imply that one would expect the fact to be the opposite of that stated; surprisingly
III) at the present moment
IV) as a sentence modifier to add slight emphasis

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: IV
Gold answer: 1
========

 No one in his right mind actually believes that we all have an equal academic potential .

II) judge or regard; look upon; judge
III) be confident about something
IV) follow a credo; have a faith; be a believer
V) credit with veracity

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: I
Gold answer: 3
========

 An additional piece of evidence from the Senate : Holding other factors constant , such as incumbency advantages and regional factors , the difference between popular votes for Republican presidential and senatorial candidates in states conducting a Senate election turns out to be a positive function of how onerous the federal government 's tax burden is per state -LRB- a progressive tax rate hits higher - income states harder -RRB- .

I) the territory occupied by one of the constituent administrative districts of a nation
II) the way something is with respect to its main attributes
III) the group of people comprising the government of a sovereign state
IV) a politically organized body of people under a single government
V) (chemistry) the three traditional states of matter are solids (fixed shape and volume) and liquids (fixed volume and shaped by the container) and gases (filling the container)
VI) a state of depression or agitation
VII) the territory occupied by a nation
VIII) the federal department in the United States that sets and maintains foreign policies

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: IV
Gold answer: 1
========

RESULT: I

II) thought that makes something comprehensible
III) the act of explaining; making something plain or intelligible

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: III
Gold answer: 1

II) the territory occupied by a nation
III) the people who live in a nation or country
IV) an area outside of cities and towns
V) a particular geographical region of indefinite boundary (usually serving some special purpose or distinguished by its people or culture or geography)

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 1
========

 Companies pre-selected to submit bids made offers that were then compared to the per barrel fee the ministry was willing to pay for boosting output above current levels at each field .

I) a position on a scale of intensity or amount or quality
II) a relative position or degree of value in a graded group
III) a specific identifiable position in a continuum or series or especially in a process
IV) height above ground
V) indicator that establishes the horizontal when a bubble is centered in a tube of liquid
VI) a flat surface at right angles to a plumb line
VII) an abstract place usually conceived as having depth
VIII) a structure consisting of a room or set of rooms at a single position along a vertical scale

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: III
Gold answer: 1
========

VI) a particular kind of commercial enterprise
VII) a particular environment or walk of life
VIII) a piece of land prepared for playing a game
IX) extensive tract of level open land
X) (mathematics) a set of elements such that addition and multiplication are commutative and associative and multiplication is distributive over addition and there are two elements 0 and 1
XI) a region in which active military operations are in progress
XII) all of the horses in a particular horse race
XIII) all the competitors in a particular contest or sporting event
XIV) a geographic region (land or sea) under which something valuable is found
XV) (computer science) a set of one or more adjacent characters comprising a unit of information

Do not provide explanations.

PROMPT: Which of the following senses is correct for the word "cases" in the following text:

 For decades , appeals courts have recognized that coverage of notorious cases can raise questions about a trial 's fairness .

I) an occurrence of something
II) a special set of circumstances
III) a comprehensive term for any proceeding in a court of law whereby an individual seeks a legal remedy
IV) the actual state of things
V) a portable container for carrying several objects
VI) a person requiring professional services
VII) a person who is subjected to experimental or other observational procedures; someone who is an object of investigation
VIII) a problem requiring investigation
IX) a statement of facts and reasons used to support an argument
X) the quantity contained in a case
XI) nouns or pronouns or adjectives (often marked by inflection) related in some way to other words in a sentence
XII) a specific state of mind that is temporary
XIII) a person of a specified kind (usually with many eccentricities)
XIV) a specific size and style of type within a type family
XV) an enveloping structure or covering enclosing an animal or plant organ or part
XVI) the housing or outer covering of something
XVII) the enclosing frame around a door or window opening
XVIII) (printing) the receptacle in which a compositor has his type, which is divided into compartments for the different letters, spaces, or numbers
XIX) bed linen consisting of a cover for a pillow
XX) a glass container used to store and display items in a shop or museum or home

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 3
========

IV) uncertainty about the truth or factuality or existence of something

Gold answer: 2

PROMPT: Which of the following senses is correct for the word "system" in the following text:

 Some 58 % agree that the market economy is the only system that will make their country developed , up from 47 % last year .

I) instrumentality that combines interrelated interacting artifacts designed to work as a coherent entity
II) a group of independent but interrelated elements comprising a unified whole
III) (physical chemistry) a sample of matter in which substances in different phases are in equilibrium
IV) a complex of methods or rules governing behavior
V) an organized structure for arranging or classifying
VI) a group of physiologically or anatomically related organs or parts
VII) a procedure or process for obtaining an objective
VIII) the living body considered as made up of interdependent components forming a unified whole
IX) an ordered manner; orderliness by virtue of being methodical and well organized

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 4

 Immigration policy under Nicolas Sarkozy was criticised from various aspects a congestion of police , legal and administrative services subjected to a policy of numbers and the compatibility of that policy with the self-proclaimed status of the country as the country of French human rights .

I) a distinct feature or element in a problem
II) a characteristic to be considered
III) the visual percept of a region
IV) the beginning or duration or completion or repetition of the action of a verb
V) the feelings expressed on a person's face

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: I
Gold answer: 2
========

II) the semantic role of an entity that is not the agent but is directly involved in or affected by the happening denoted by the verb in the clause

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 1

 The Foundation recently published a comparative study as part of the EPOC project which assesses the extent to which direct participation can humanise work while increasing profitability .

I) a detailed critical inspection
II) applying the mind to learning and understanding a subject (especially by reading)
III) a written document describing the findings of some individual or group
IV) a state of deep mental absorption
V) a room used for reading and writing and studying
VI) a branch of knowledge
VII) preliminary drawing for later elaboration
VIII) attentive consideration and meditation
IX) someone who memorizes quickly and easily (as the lines for a part in a play)
X) a composition intended to develop one aspect of the performer's technique

Do not provide explanations.
RESULT: II
Gold answer: 3
========
